passage_text: We are a district of approximately 2900 students supported by a community deeply committed to quality education. Our district prides itself for excellence in academic performance; but it is equally proud of our student performance in the arts, athletics, as well as our students’ contributions to their community.

Jamesville-DeWitt High School students present 'The Wedding Singer' as spring high school musical. Jamesville-DeWitt Little Shop of Horrors. Jamesville-DeWitt High School students rehearse for their spring 2015 high school musical The Wedding Singer. high school musicals 2015 (Submitted photo by Mark Kotzin).

View/Post Comments. Students at Jamesville-DeWitt High School will be the first local school to perform 'The Wedding Singer' as their spring 2015 high school musical 7 p.m. Thursday, Friday and Saturday, Feb. 5, 6 and 7 in the high school's Osborn Auditorium, 6845 Edinger Drive, DeWitt, NY 13214.
